    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# LoRA Training and Backpropagation Explained\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook provides a visual explanation of how LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation) works in fine-tuning diffusion models.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## What is LoRA?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation) is a parameter-efficient fine-tuning method that:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Freezes the pre-trained model weights (keeping all knowledge)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Injects trainable rank decomposition matrices into each layer\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Dramatically reduces the number of trainable parameters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Results in small, portable \\\"adapter\\\" weights\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This makes it possible to fine-tune billion-parameter models like SDXL on consumer hardware.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Helper function to display diagrams and images\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from IPython.display import HTML, Image, display\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import base64\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from io import BytesIO\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Try to install matplotlib if not available\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    import matplotlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(\\\"Installing matplotlib...\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    !pip install matplotlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 1. The LoRA Architecture\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"In a neural network, each layer typically has a weight matrix $W$ that transforms inputs. LoRA decomposes the weight updates into two smaller matrices $A$ and $B$:\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Create a visual diagram of LoRA architecture\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Define colors\\n\",\n",
    "    \"colors = {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'frozen': '#d4f1f9',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'trainable': '#ffcccc',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'output': '#d9f2d9'\\n\",\n",
    "    \"}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Original path - frozen weights\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.5, 0.8, 'Original Model', fontsize=14, ha='center')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.5, 0.6, 'Input → W → Output', fontsize=12, ha='center')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.5, 0.4, 'Large Weight Matrix W', fontsize=12, ha='center', \\n\",\n",
    "    \"         bbox=dict(facecolor=colors['frozen'], alpha=0.5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.5, 0.2, '[FROZEN]', fontsize=10, ha='center')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.axis('off')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# LoRA path\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.5, 0.9, 'With LoRA', fontsize=14, ha='center')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.5, 0.75, 'Input', fontsize=12, ha='center')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.annotate('', xy=(0.3, 0.65), xytext=(0.5, 0.7), \\n\",\n",
    "    \"             arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', lw=1.5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.annotate('', xy=(0.7, 0.65), xytext=(0.5, 0.7), \\n\",\n",
    "    \"             arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', lw=1.5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Original path\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.3, 0.6, 'Original W', fontsize=10, ha='center',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        bbox=dict(facecolor=colors['frozen'], alpha=0.5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.3, 0.5, '[FROZEN]', fontsize=8, ha='center')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.annotate('', xy=(0.3, 0.35), xytext=(0.3, 0.45), \\n\",\n",
    "    \"             arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', lw=1.5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# LoRA path\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.7, 0.6, 'Matrix A', fontsize=10, ha='center',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        bbox=dict(facecolor=colors['trainable'], alpha=0.5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.7, 0.5, '[TRAINABLE]', fontsize=8, ha='center')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.annotate('', xy=(0.7, 0.4), xytext=(0.7, 0.45), \\n\",\n",
    "    \"             arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', lw=1.5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.7, 0.35, 'Matrix B', fontsize=10, ha='center',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        bbox=dict(facecolor=colors['trainable'], alpha=0.5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.7, 0.25, '[TRAINABLE]', fontsize=8, ha='center')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.annotate('', xy=(0.7, 0.15), xytext=(0.7, 0.2), \\n\",\n",
    "    \"             arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', lw=1.5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.7, 0.1, f'× (α/r)', fontsize=10, ha='center')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.annotate('', xy=(0.5, 0.05), xytext=(0.7, 0.05), \\n\",\n",
    "    \"             arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', lw=1.5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.annotate('', xy=(0.5, 0.05), xytext=(0.3, 0.05), \\n\",\n",
    "    \"             arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', lw=1.5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.5, 0, 'Output = Original + LoRA', fontsize=10, ha='center',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        bbox=dict(facecolor=colors['output'], alpha=0.5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.axis('off')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Key Formula\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The LoRA update can be expressed mathematically as:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"$$W' = W + \\\\Delta W = W + BA \\\\cdot \\\\frac{\\\\alpha}{r}$$\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Where:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- $W$ is the original weight matrix (frozen)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- $\\\\Delta W$ is the update (BA product)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- $B$ and $A$ are low-rank matrices (trainable)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- $r$ is the rank (typically 4-128)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- $\\\\alpha$ is a scaling factor (typically 1-128)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 2. Parameter Efficiency\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"For a weight matrix $W \\\\in \\\\mathbb{R}^{d \\\\times k}$, we use LoRA matrices $B \\\\in \\\\mathbb{R}^{d \\\\times r}$ and $A \\\\in \\\\mathbb{R}^{r \\\\times k}$ where $r \\\\ll \\\\min(d, k)$.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Let's calculate the parameter savings:\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Example parameter count calculation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"d = 768  # Hidden dimension (common in SDXL layers)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"k = 768  # Same dimension for simplicity (square matrix)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"r = 16   # LoRA rank\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Parameters in original matrix W\\n\",\n",
    "    \"original_params = d * k\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Parameters in LoRA matrices A and B\\n\",\n",
    "    \"lora_params = r * k + d * r\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Comparison\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Original matrix parameters: {original_params:,}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"LoRA matrices parameters: {lora_params:,}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Parameter reduction: {original_params / lora_params:.2f}x\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"LoRA is {100 * lora_params / original_params:.2f}% of original size\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Visualize with bar chart\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"bars = plt.bar(['Original W', 'LoRA (A+B)'], [original_params, lora_params], color=[colors['frozen'], colors['trainable']])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.yscale('log')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.title('Parameter Count Comparison (log scale)')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.ylabel('Number of Parameters')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Add value labels on top of bars\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for bar in bars:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    height = bar.get_height()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2., height,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            f'{height:,}',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            ha='center', va='bottom', rotation=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 3. Training Process Flow\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"In the context of SDXL training, LoRA fits into the diffusion model denoising process:\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Create a diagram of the LoRA training process\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"processes = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Load Image & Caption\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Encode to Latent Space (VAE)\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Add Random Noise\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"UNet Predicts Noise\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Compare with Original Noise\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Calculate Loss\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Backpropagate through UNet\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Calculate gradients for LoRA A & B\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Update LoRA matrices\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Next Training Step\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Process colors\\n\",\n",
    "    \"colors_map = {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    0: '#f9d5e5',  # Data prep\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    1: '#f9d5e5',  # Data prep\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    2: '#f9d5e5',  # Data prep\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    3: '#eeeeee',  # Forward\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    4: '#eeeeee',  # Forward\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    5: '#eeeeee',  # Forward\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    6: '#d4f1f9',  # Backward\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    7: '#d4f1f9',  # Backward\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    8: '#d4f1f9',  # Backward\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    9: '#d9f2d9',  # Next\\n\",\n",
    "    \"}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Draw the process flow\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i, process in enumerate(processes):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    y_pos = 0.9 - i * 0.08\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    plt.text(0.1, y_pos, f\\\"{i+1}. {process}\\\", fontsize=12,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"             bbox=dict(facecolor=colors_map[i], alpha=0.5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Draw arrow connecting steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if i < len(processes) - 1:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        plt.annotate('', xy=(0.1, 0.9 - (i+1) * 0.08 + 0.02), xytext=(0.1, y_pos - 0.02), \\n\",\n",
    "    \"                     arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', lw=1.5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.5, 0.95, 'LoRA Training Process for Diffusion Models', fontsize=14, ha='center')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Add some explanatory notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"notes = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.6, 0.82, \\\"Original UNet weights remain frozen\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.6, 0.74, \\\"Only LoRA matrices A and B are trainable\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.6, 0.66, \\\"Noise prediction task is the same as in normal diffusion training\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.6, 0.58, \\\"Mean Squared Error between predicted and actual noise\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.6, 0.42, \\\"Gradients only update the small adapter matrices\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.6, 0.34, \\\"Parameter efficiency: ~99% fewer parameters to update\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.6, 0.26, \\\"Resulting LoRA weights are small enough to share easily\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for x, y, note in notes:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    plt.text(x, y, note, fontsize=10, va='center',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            bbox=dict(facecolor='#f9f9f9', alpha=0.5, boxstyle='round,pad=0.5'))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.axis('off')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 4. Backpropagation Through LoRA\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"During training, the gradients flow through the network and update only the LoRA parameters:\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Create a backpropagation diagram\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Main flow\\n\",\n",
    "    \"steps = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.5, 0.9, \\\"Loss Function\\\", colors['output']),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.5, 0.7, \\\"UNet Output\\\", '#eeeeee'),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.3, 0.5, \\\"Original Weights (Frozen)\\\", colors['frozen']),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.7, 0.5, \\\"BA Product\\\", colors['trainable']),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.7, 0.3, \\\"LoRA Matrix B\\\", colors['trainable']),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.3, 0.3, \\\"LoRA Matrix A\\\", colors['trainable']),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.7, 0.1, \\\"Updated Matrix B\\\", colors['output']),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.3, 0.1, \\\"Updated Matrix A\\\", colors['output']),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Draw boxes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for x, y, label, color in steps:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    plt.text(x, y, label, fontsize=11, ha='center', va='center',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"             bbox=dict(facecolor=color, alpha=0.5, boxstyle='round,pad=0.5'))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Draw connections with gradient labels\\n\",\n",
    "    \"connections = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.5, 0.85, 0.5, 0.75, \\\"∂L/∂y\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.45, 0.65, 0.35, 0.55, \\\"∂L/∂W_original\\\\n(not used)\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.55, 0.65, 0.65, 0.55, \\\"∂L/∂BA\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.65, 0.45, 0.65, 0.35, \\\"∂L/∂B\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.65, 0.45, 0.35, 0.35, \\\"∂L/∂A\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.65, 0.25, 0.65, 0.15, \\\"B_new = B - lr × ∂L/∂B\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (0.35, 0.25, 0.35, 0.15, \\\"A_new = A - lr × ∂L/∂A\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for x1, y1, x2, y2, label in connections:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    plt.annotate(label, xy=(x2, y2+0.05), xytext=(x1, y1-0.05), \\n\",\n",
    "    \"                 arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', lw=1.5),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                 fontsize=9, ha='center')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.title('Backpropagation Through LoRA', fontsize=14)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.text(0.5, -0.05, \\\"Only LoRA matrices A and B are updated during backpropagation\\\", \\n\",\n",
    "    \"         fontsize=11, ha='center', va='center',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"         bbox=dict(facecolor='#f9f9f9', alpha=0.5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.axis('off')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 5. PyTorch Implementation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Here's a simple PyTorch implementation of a LoRA layer:\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import torch\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import torch.nn as nn\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import math\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"class LoRALayer(nn.Module):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    def __init__(self, in_dim, out_dim, rank=16, alpha=32):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        super().__init__()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        self.original_layer = nn.Linear(in_dim, out_dim, bias=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\n\",\n",
    "    \"        # Special initialization as in the LoRA paper\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        self.lora_A = nn.Parameter(torch.randn(rank, in_dim) / math.sqrt(rank))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        self.lora_B = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros(out_dim, rank))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\n\",\n",
    "    \"        # Scaling factor\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        self.scale = alpha / rank\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\n\",\n",
    "    \"        # Freeze the original weights\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        for param in self.original_layer.parameters():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            param.requires_grad = False\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    def forward(self, x):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        # Original output\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        original_output = self.original_layer(x)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\n\",\n",
    "    \"        # LoRA output\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        # The BA product creates the effective weight update\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        lora_output = (self.lora_B @ self.lora_A) @ x.T\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        lora_output = lora_output.T  # Transpose to match dimensions\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\n\",\n",
    "    \"        # Combined output\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return original_output + lora_output * self.scale\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Example usage\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if torch.cuda.is_available():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(\\\"CUDA is available, example will run on GPU\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    device = torch.device(\\\"cuda\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"else:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(\\\"CUDA not available, example will run on CPU\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    device = torch.device(\\\"cpu\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Create a small example\\n\",\n",
    "    \"lora_layer = LoRALayer(768, 768, rank=16, alpha=32).to(device)\\n\",\n",
